I meant that people voting against a failed Proposal receive an award.

This is not unlike the original Terrible Proposals scam on Nomic World,
the MUD-based predecessor to Agora.  In Nomic World, Proposals had
to be seconded to be put up for vote.  If you were asked to second a
Proposal, you had three options: second it, privately refuse to second
it, or publically refuse to second it.  Now, the proposer of a proposal
received an F-A award or penalty.  Players who seconded a passing
proposal, or publically refused to second a failed proposal, received
two poitns each.

A group of about 6 people got together and proposed a series of
terrible proposals, with one person seconding each proposal, and
the rest publically refusing to second it.  Thus, they ended up with
a net gain of points.

Steve posted the text of the TPs not too long ago, and I think I
still have them--I'll repost for the benefit of the new players.

